data.title: Chicago Bulls Roster
data.meta_description: Chicago Bulls scores, news, schedule, players, stats, rumors, depth charts and more on RealGM.com
data.text:
Taj Gibson was selected as the #26 pick in the First Round of the 2009 NBA Draft by the Chicago Bulls. Taj Gibson signed a multi-year contract with the Chicago Bulls on July 8, 2009.

Joakim Noah was selected as the #9 pick in the First Round of the 2007 NBA Draft by the Chicago Bulls. Joakim Noah signed a multi-year contract with the Chicago Bulls on July 24, 2007. Joakim Noah signed a multi-year extension with the Chicago Bulls on September 30, 2010.

Derrick Rose was selected as the #1 pick in the First Round of the 2008 NBA Draft by the Chicago Bulls. Derrick Rose signed a multi-year contract with the Chicago Bulls on July 1, 2008.

Draft Rights to Omer Asik, the #6 pick in the Second Round of the 2008 NBA Draft, were acquired by the Chicago Bulls from the Portland Trail Blazers on June 26, 2008. Omer Asik signed a multi-year contract with the Chicago Bulls on July 9, 2010.

Draft Rights to Luol Deng, the #7 pick in the First Round of the 2004 NBA Draft, were acquired by the Chicago Bulls from the Phoenix Suns on June 24, 2004. Luol Deng signed a multi-year contract with the Chicago Bulls on July 16, 2004. Luol Deng re-signed to a multi-year contract as a free agent with the Chicago Bulls on July 31, 2008.

Carlos Boozer was acquired in a sign and trade by the Chicago Bulls from the Utah Jazz on July 8, 2010.

C.J. Watson was acquired in a sign and trade by the Chicago Bulls from the Golden State Warriors on July 19, 2010.

Keith Bogans signed a multi-year contract as a free agent with the Chicago Bulls on August 10, 2010.

Ronnie Brewer signed a multi-year contract as a free agent with the Chicago Bulls on July 22, 2010.

Rasual Butler signed a contract as a free agent with the Chicago Bulls on March 3, 2011.

Kyle Korver signed a multi-year contract as a free agent with the Chicago Bulls on July 9, 2010.

John Lucas signed a multi-year contract as a free agent with the Chicago Bulls on March 20, 2011.

Jannero Pargo signed a multi-year contract as a free agent with the Chicago Bulls on March 20, 2011.

Brian Scalabrine signed a contract as a free agent with the Chicago Bulls on September 27, 2010.

Kurt Thomas signed a contract as a free agent with the Chicago Bulls on July 26, 2010.
